    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.34.36-38_0001" />
                <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection</note>                                               <fw type="curatorial">36</fw>
                <note type="curatorial">150-2</note>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                <hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF MISSOURI</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA</hi>
                    <lb/>
                
                
                <hi rend="caps">COLLEGE OF ARTS AND SCIENCE</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">DEPARTMENT OF ENGLISH</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                Skyrim, Rt. 7
                Dec 19, '61
                    </dateline>
                
                <salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I'm so eager to hear how Lucile is. I do hope she may soon be at home with you and Stewart, and well enough to say hello <add>to</add> me. You must have been terribly worried.</p>
                
                <p>I rec'd a copy of the letter Frank Mott wrote about the essay on my stuff. I'm afraid he does
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.34.36-38_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">37</fw>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    not feel very well.</p>
                
                <p>I wish you and Lucile could have been at the unveiling ceremony at the State Capitol in Lincoln, Neb. It was a perfect event.</p>
                
                <p>I think a great deal about you three, and I'll be so glad when I know everything is all right again.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately</salute>
                
                <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
                
            </div1>
            
            
            
